</mei>

<!--
VOICING PLAN:
Holy God, We Praise Thy Name — F major (1 flat: Bb). 3/4 meter.
All B notes carry accid.ges="f" for the key signature Bb.

Phrase 1 (mm. 1-8): Light texture. m1 RH uses just 2 notes (A4 C5), LH has open F3-A3-C4 root.
  m2 uses IΔ to introduce 7th chord color early. m3 V7 "333" with Bb3 in LH.
  m7 beat-by-beat IV→V→I progression emphasizes the descending melodic line.
  m8 uses quartal "44" on V before V7 — open sound before cadential arrival.

Phrase 2 (mm. 9-12): Richer. m10 uses iii (Am in F = degree 3) as a passing chord,
  giving LH the motion E3-G3-Bb3-D4 (iii7 = Am7 in F). m12 climbs to F5 in RH.

Phrase 3 (mm. 13-16): Contrasting ii-V motion. m13-14 ii "333" G3-Bb3-D4-F4 is the
  heaviest LH so far. m16 pure V held dotted-half, building to phrase 4.

Phrase 4 (mm. 17-20): Climax. m17 IVΔ "333" Bb3-D4-F4-A4 — the highest 4-note LH.
  m19 IV→iii→V7 in each beat — most harmonic activity of the piece.
  m20 F1 pedal + IΔ in LH (F3-A3-C4-E4) + I "334" in RH (F4-A4-C5-F5) = maximum density.

TEXTURE ARC:
Light (2-note RH) → 3-note RH → IV "334" 4-note RH at final cadence.
LH grows from open "334" triads → "333" 7th chords → IVΔ at climax → F1 pedal final.
Rhythmic variety: half+quarter in most bars; all-quarter movement in developmental mm. (m2, m7, m10, m19).
